## Docker
This project includes a `Dockerfile` that builds and runs the Swing app.

> Note: Docker desktop/GUI forwarding is environment-specific. The container will start the Java app; you may need X11/Wayland forwarding for GUI display depending on your host setup.

### 1) Pull the Docker image
If you already pushed the image to a registry, use:

```bash
docker pull /: ```

### 2) Run the image as a container
```bash
docker run --rm -it /: ```

### 3) Create a container from the image
```bash
docker create --name bmi-calculator /: ```

### 4) Start the created container
```bash
docker start bmi-calculator
```

### 5) Stop a running container
```bash
docker stop bmi-calculator
```

